{{Infobox company | name = Integrated Utility Services IUS | logo = | type = Subsidiary | foundation = 1996 | location = [[Yorkshire]], [[UK]] | key_people = | industry = [[Energy]] | products = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = 134 | parent = [[Berkshire Hathaway Energy]] | homepage =[http://www.ius.co.uk/ IUS] }}
'''Integrated Utility Services''' is a high voltage electrical contracting business owned by an [[electrical distribution]] company and is based in [[Yorkshire]] in England. It is owned by '''Northern Electric Distribution Limited''' ('''NEDL''') and '''Yorkshire Electricity Distribution plc''' ('''YEDL''') which are the [[Distribution Network Operator]]s for the North East England and Yorkshire regions.
==History== The company was created after the takeover of [[Northern Electric]] by [[MidAmerican Energy Holdings Company|CalEnergy]] in 1996.<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/northern-electric-sparks-pounds-650m-us-bid-1360778.html Northern Electric sparks £650m US bid] The Independent, 29 October 1996</ref> The company disposed of the supply business of Northern Electric to [[Innogy]] in 2001 in exchange for the distribution business of [[Yorkshire Electricity]].<ref>[http://pepei.pennnet.com/articles/article_display.cfm?article_id=119189 Innogy, Northern in retail swap] Power Engineering International, September 2001</ref>
