{{Infobox power station |name = José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station |image = Nuclear power station in Almonacid de Zorita (Spain).jpg |image_caption = Zorita NPP |location_map = Spain |country = Spain | coordinates = {{coord|40|20|57|N|2|53|4|W|region:ES_type:landmark_source:dewiki|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[Unión Fenosa|Union Fenosa Generation S.A.]] |operator = [[Union Electrica Fenosa]], S.A. |construction_began = 1964 |commissioned = August 13, 1969 |decommissioned = April 30, 2006 |ps_units_decommissioned = 1 x 150 [[Megawatt|MW]] |ps_annual_generation = 392 [[GWh]] |website = }} The '''José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station''' (also known as '''Zorita'''<ref>[http://www.foronuclear.org/en/2004_a_year_of_nuclear_energy.jsp ::FORO Nuclear::<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>) was a [[nuclear power station]] in [[Almonacid de Zorita]], {{convert|70|km}} east of [[Madrid]], [[Spain]].
The power plant consisted of a single [[pressurized water reactor|PWR]] of 160&nbsp;MWe, built by [[Westinghouse Electric Company]]. It was operated by [[Unión Fenosa]].<ref name=wnn120210>{{cite news | url = http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/WR_Jose_Cabrera_moves_into_decommissioning_1202101.html | publisher=World Nuclear News | date=2010-02-11 | title= José Cabrera moves into decommissioning | accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref>
==History== Construction of the power station started in 1964. It was commissioned in 1968, and it operated from 1968 until 2006. In 2006, it was closed by ministerial order.<ref name=wnn120210/>
On 11 February 2010, Unión Fenosa transferred the site's ownership to Enresa, a Spanish company responsible for decommissioning the power station. Enresa planned to clear the site by the end of 2015.<ref name=wnn120210/>
==2003 incident==
The [[Spanish Nuclear Safety Council]] has investigated the plant's deficient [[Nuclear safety|safety system]] and a missing screw that prevented the reactor from resuming operations after a month-long refueling operation in December 2003.{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}}
==Decommissioning== Westinghouse Electric Company has secured a contract for dismantling and segmentation of the Jose Cabrera nuclear power station.
