{{Infobox power station |name = Titiokura/Te Waka Wind Farm |image = |location = [[Hawke's Bay]] |location_map = New Zealand |country = New Zealand | coordinates = {{coord|39|12|20|S|176|41|13|E|type:landmark_region:NZ|display=inline,title}} |owner = [[Unison Networks]] |status = P |ps_units_operational= up to 49 |ps_electrical_capacity= up to 147 MW |commissioned = |decommissioned = }}
The '''Titiokura/Te Waka Wind Farm''' was a [[wind farm]] project abandoned by [[Unison Networks]] and Roaring 40s. It was to be located adjacent to [[New Zealand State Highway 5|SH5]] in the Te Pohue - Titiokura area, 35&nbsp;km west of [[Napier, New Zealand|Napier]], [[New Zealand]].<ref name="windenergy">{{cite web|url=http://windenergy.org.nz/nz-wind-farms/proposed-wind-farms/te-waka-and-titiokura |publisher=NZWEA|title=Te Waka and Titiokura wind farm}}</ref>
Stage 1 of the project, Titiokura, gained resource consents in 2006 after an [[Environment Court of New Zealand|Environment Court]] appeal. This stage is for 15 wind turbines, producing up to 45 MW.
Stage 2, Te Waka, was to have a capacity of up to 102 MW from 34 turbines.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unison.co.nz/site_resources/library/OUR%20COMMUNITY/Titiokura_Te_Waka_Wind_Farm_aug_08.pdf |publisher=Unison |title=Titiokura/Te Waka Wind Farm |date=August 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081014101952/http://unison.co.nz/site_resources/library/OUR%20COMMUNITY/Titiokura_Te_Waka_Wind_Farm_aug_08.pdf |archivedate=2008-10-14 |df= }}</ref> The Environment Court declined this application, after the hearing was held in December 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.courts.govt.nz/environment/legislation-and-resources/decisions/Unison_Networks_v_HDC_Decision.pdf|title=Decision of the Environment Court: Unison Networks v Hastings District Council|date=30 January 2009}}</ref> A revised proposal was prepared, this was declined by the Environment Court in February 2009.<ref name="windenergy" />
Early stages of the consent process were administered by the [[Hastings, New Zealand|Hastings]] District Council and the [[Hawke's Bay (region)|Hawke's Bay]] Regional Council. Both stages of the wind farm are opposed by local [[iwi]], Ngati Hineuru and Maungaharuru-Tangitu Society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/4787696a6045.html?source=RSShawkesbay/headlines_20081210 |title=Iwi felt harassed on wind farm plan|publisher=Dominion Post|date=10 December 2008}}</ref>
