{{Infobox tornado year |name = Tornadoes of 1968 |image = |caption = |timespan = January –December 1968 |max_F = F5 |max_location = 4 locations |max_date = 3 different days |tornadoes_usa = 657<ref>http://www.tornadohistoryproject.com/tornado/1968/map</ref> |total_damages_usa = Unknown |total_fatalities_usa= 131 |total_fatalities_world = >131 |year=1968 }}
This page documents the '''[[tornado]]es and [[tornado outbreak]]s of 1968''', primarily in the United States. Most tornadoes form in the U.S., although some events may take place internationally. Tornado statistics for older years like this often appear significantly lower than modern years due to fewer reports or confirmed tornadoes. 2 F5 tornadoes struck Iowa in the Charles City and Maynard areas, combined they claimed 18 lives and this was one of very few cases in history where two F5s or EF5 tornadoes hit the same state, on the same day. {{Clear}}
